  "texts": [
    "The same draw call is able to render two different views of the scene, each one with a different camera orientation, which are stored in two different textures.",
    "Lately, it has been improved for GPUs with Turing architecture, enabling the rendering of four different views for ultra-wide FOV.",
    "These new features can be accessed through the extension named OVR_multiview (NVIDIACorporation 2018; Unterguggenberger et al. 2020) in the OpenGL standard (Open Graphics Library), Vulkan, DirectX11 and DirectX12.",
    "However, MVR still requires multiple fragment shader calls despite using one pass.",
    "With this in mind, Unterguggenberger et al. (2020) explores the latency derived from MVR with a flexible framework that proposes several possibilities regarding geometry instancing, framebuffers as well as culling and clipping."
  ],
